'''Angier Buchanan Duke''' (1884&ndash;1923) was a trustee of [[Duke University]] from 1914&ndash;1923, as well as vice president and president of its Alumni Association.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://library.duke.edu/lilly/about/lillyartproj/angier-buchanan-duke.html |title=Angier Buchanan Duke |quote= |publisher=[[Duke University]] |accessdate=2008-07-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501112730/http://library.duke.edu/lilly/about/lillyartproj/angier-buchanan-duke.html |archivedate=2008-05-01 }}</ref>
==Biography== Duke was the son of [[Benjamin Newton Duke]] and Sarah Pearson Angier. He was the brother of [[Mary Lillian Duke]], and first cousin to the flamboyant heiress [[Doris Duke]] (1912&ndash;1993). He married Cordelia Drexel Biddle (daughter of bank heir [[Anthony Joseph Drexel Biddle, Sr.]]) with whom he had two children, [[Angier Biddle Duke]] (1915&ndash;1995) and Anthony Drexel Duke (1918-2014). In an accident in 1905 he had lost a hand and part of his arm. In 1923 he drowned when a boat overturned and he was unable to get back into the boat because of his missing hand.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.harnett.org/library/Biographies/dukebn.doc|title=Notable Harnett County Residents: B. N. Duke |quote= |publisher=[[Harnett County Public Library]] |accessdate=2010-03-23 }}</ref> [[John Davidson (entertainer)|John Davidson]] portrayed him in the 1967 film, ''[[The Happiest Millionaire]]''.
